article.description: Jack Purchase made five 3-pointers and scored 21 points to help Hawaii beat Delaware State 77-66 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Hawaii hits 9 3s in 1st half, beats Delaware State 77-66
article.linkText: Hawaii hits 9 3s in 1st half, beats Delaware State 77-66
article.story: HONOLULU -- Jack Purchase made five 3-pointers and scored 21 points to help Hawaii beat Delaware State 77-66 on Thursday night. Purchase made Hawaii's sixth 3-pointer of the first half with 9:38 left for a 24-19 lead and the Rainbow Warriors took their first double-digit lead with less than two minutes left on Ido Flaisher's putback. Hawaii had a 41-27 lead at the break after making 9 of 20 from beyond the arc. Purchase tied his career high with 21 on a layup with 3:45 left to extend Hawaii's lead to 68-52. The Rainbow Warriors only made one 3 in the second half but led by as many as 20. Sheriff Drammeh added 12 points and Leland Green scored 11 for Hawaii (6-7). Purchase also grabbed eight boards to help Hawaii outrebound Delaware State 35-21. Devin Morgan hit four 3s and scored 26 points and DeAndre Haywood added 16 points for Delaware State (3-12), which lost its fourth straight.
